OL,3,CThe secret footage from Warwickshire
OL,4,Cabattoir under police investigation
OL,6,FWe were told by locals for more than
OL,7,F100 years it used to be a small family-
OL,8,Fowned abattoir with an on-site
OL,9,Fbutchers, which would sell meat to
OL,10,Fmany of the villagers.
OL,12,FCarolyn McKay, a local resident,
OL,13,Festimated that at its peak, around 200
OL,14,Fanimals were arriving to be
OL,15,Fslaughtered there every week.
OL,17,FIn 2023 however, the abattoir was
OL,18,Fbought by new owners who closed the
OL,19,Fbutchers but expanded the
OL,20,Fslaughterhouse, with operations
OL,21,Fbeginning in April 2024.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/14
